The person is experiencing a heavy feeling of distress or negativity.

journal_entries.text: I feel really sick and cannot wait to get out of Gainesville
journal_entries.summary: The writer is feeling unwell and longing to leave Gainesville.

journal_entries.text: The Gators just won the national championship!!!! I am so happy to be a Gator and I cannot wait to celebrate with my friends. I am so thrilled right now
journal_entries.summary: The writer is feeling extremely joyous and excited about the Gators' win in the national championship and is looking forward to celebrating this victory.

journal_entries.text: I'm really nervous for my upcoming chemistry exam. This exam is worth about 20% of my grade and I am feeling vastly underprepared for the test.
journal_entries.summary: Expressing anxiety and fear about an upcoming chemistry exam.

journal_entries.text: I just finished taking my test, and I actually think it went pretty well. I hope to get maybe an 80%, but honestly it was a lot easier than the practice test.
journal_entries.summary: Feeling hopeful and relieved after a test, comparing it to a practice test.

journal_entries.text: I just got my Chemistry Exam score back and turns out I got a 100!!!! I am so excited because now I only need to get about a 60% on the final to keep my A. Lets goooooo
journal_entries.summary: The writer is ecstatic about scoring 100 on their Chemistry Exam and is looking forward to maintaining their A with the final exam.
